[2026-07-11T15:20:21.500Z] [STDOUT] {"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045/events","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045","id":4862533972,"node_id":"I_kwDOPUU0qc8AAAABIdRhVA","number":2045,"title":"Disk gate: change default HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD 0.8→0.65 for safer headroom on isolation hosts","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-07-11T13:50:39Z","updated_at":"2026-07-11T13:50:39Z","closed_at":null,"assignee":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Request\n\nChange the default disk queue-admission threshold from **0.8 → 0.65**.\n\n`HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` currently defaults to `0.8` (set in #1981, raised from the older `0.9`). In practice `0.8` still leaves too little headroom on disk-constrained isolation hosts — tasks continue to be launched at 80% used and then die at ~100% while a `--isolation docker` task expands images/scratch. Operators keep having to manually lower it to `0.65` in their env to get a safe margin.\n\n## Where\n\n`src/queue-config.lib.mjs`:\n\n```js\n// line ~250 (thresholds.disk)\ndisk: getThresholdConfig('disk', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_STRATEGY', 0.8, 'enqueue'),\n// line ~266 (legacy flat DISK_THRESHOLD)\nDISK_THRESHOLD: getThresholdConfig('disk', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_STRATEGY', 0.8, 'enqueue').value,\n```\n\nBoth `0.8` default literals should become `0.65`.\n\n## Why 0.65\n\n- `--isolation docker` tasks need substantial free disk for image layers + per-task scratch; starting at 80% used routinely fills the host before a task completes.\n- `0.65` is the value operators already fall back to manually (e.g. the hive-control-center deployment), so making it the default removes a required override.\n- The `enqueue` strategy is unchanged — tasks wait rather than being rejected, so a lower threshold just means the bot backs off earlier and resumes once disk frees up.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Update the two default literals above.\n- Update any doc/comment referencing the `0.8` default (e.g. the `Issue #1981` comment block).\n- No env-var/API change — operators can still override via `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` or `HIVE_MIND_QUEUE_CONFIG`.\n\nFollow-up to #1981.\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null,"pinned_comment":null}
