nstead of 90%).\\n2. **`HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB` default `2048` → `10240`** (require ≥10 GB free to start a task, instead of 2 GB).\\n\\nBoth knobs **already exist** — this issue only asks to change their built-in defaults to safer values. (An earlier revision of this issue proposed adding a *new* `HIVE_MIND_MIN_FREE_DISK_GB` var; that was a mistake — `HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB` already provides the absolute free-space gate, in MB. No new var is needed.)\\n\\n### Motivation\\n\\nOn a real deployment the disk filled to ~96–100% and **isolated tasks died because resources were exhausted** (`/dev/sda1 96G, 4.1G free, 96%`). The current defaults are too permissive:\\n- 90% used on a ~96 GB disk only blocks with ~9.6 GB free — too little headroom once several multi-GB isolation tasks are mid-build (Rust `target/`, `node_modules/onnxruntime`+CUDA, cloned repos).\\n- The absolute floor of 2 GB is far too low for docker-isolation tasks that each need many GB.\\n\\nThese two defaults are what we set locally via `.lenv` to stop the bleeding (`HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD: 0.8`, `HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB: 10240`); this issue asks to make those the shipped defaults so every deployment is protected without per-host overrides.\\n\\n## Change 1 — `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` default `0.9` → `0.8`\\n\\nSet in `src/queue-config.lib.mjs`, in **two** places that must change in lockstep:\\n\\n`src/queue-config.lib.mjs:252` (primary `thresholds.disk`):\\n```js\\ndisk: getThresholdConfig('disk', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_STRATEGY', 0.9, 'reject'),\\n```\\n`src/queue-config.lib.mjs:268` (legacy flat alias):\\n```js\\nDISK_THRESHOLD: getThresholdConfig('disk', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_STRATEGY', 0.9, 'reject').value,\\n```\\n→ change both `0.9` to `0.8`.\\n\\nThis default also drives the display marker: `DISPLAY_THRESHOLDS.DISK = thresholdToPercent(QUEUE_CONFIG.DISK_THRESHOLD)` (`src/queue-config.lib.mjs:311`), used by the `/limits` \\\"Disk space … ⚠️\\\" bar (`src/limits.lib.mjs:1037-1042`). So changing the default to `0.8` moves both the launch-blocking decision **and** the ⚠️ warning marker to 80%, in lockstep. (The `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` env var and the LINO `HIVE_MIND_QUEUE_CONFIG` still override the default — this only changes the built-in fallback.)\\n\\nIt is a float ratio (0–1), so the default literal is `0.8` (not `80`).\\n\\n## Change 2 — `HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB` default `2048` → `10240`\\n\\nSet in `src/config.lib.mjs:114`:\\n```js\\nexport const systemLimits = {\\n  minDiskSpaceMb: parseIntWithDefault('HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB', 2048),\\n  ...\\n};\\n```\\n→ change `2048` to `10240` (10 GB, in MB — units confirmed by `docs/CONFIGURATION.md:82`: \\\"Minimum required disk space in MB\\\"). This gate is consumed by the task-start path (`src/memory-check.mjs`, `src/hive.mjs`).\\n\\nRemember to update the documented default in `docs/CONFIGURATION.md` (and the localized `CONFIGURATION.{hi,zh,ru}.md`) from 2048 → 10240, and any `coolify/.env.example` reference.\\n\\n## Resulting defaults\\n\\n| Var | Old default | New default | Units | Meaning |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` | 0.9 | **0.8** | float ratio 0–1 | block when usage ≥ this |\\n| `HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB` | 2048 | **10240** | MB | block unless ≥ this much free |\\n\\nA task is blocked if **either** gate trips (≥80% used **or** <10 GB free). On large disks the GB floor bites first; on small disks the percentage does — both are protective.\\n\\n## Citations\\n- `src/queue-config.lib.mjs:252, :268` — disk threshold default `0.9` → `0.8`; `:298,:311` display derivation.\\n- `src/config.lib.mjs:114` — `minDiskSpaceMb` default `2048` → `10240`; consumed by `src/memory-check.mjs`, `src/hive.mjs`.\\n- `docs/CONFIGURATION.md:82` — documented default (update to 10240); localized copies `CONFIGURATION.{hi,zh,ru}.md`.\\n- `src/limits.lib.mjs:549` `getDiskSpaceInfo` (returns `availableMB`/`availableBytes`/`freePercentage`); `:1037-1042` disk display bar + ⚠️.\\n- `src/telegram-solve-queue.lib.mjs:801-826` — the percentage admission gate (uses `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD`).\\n\\n## Related\\n- #1979 (auto-reap finished task containers) and #1980 (make `hive-cleanup` docker-aware) — those reclaim space; this prevents launching into an already-full disk. Complementary: reaping reduces how often the gate trips; the gate is the backstop when it would still overflow.\\n- Upstream `link-foundation/start#140` (container removal default).\\n\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-24T12:14:18Z\",\"labels\":[],\"number\":1981,\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"Disk gate: change defaults — HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD 0.9→0.8 and HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB 2048→10240 (10 GB)\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-06-24T23:13:17Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1981\"}\n--\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/raw-data/issue-1981-comments.json:1:[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4789278821\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1981#issuecomment-4789278821\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1981\",\"id\":4789278821,\"node_id\":\"IC_kwDOPUU0qc8AAAABHXaYZQ\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"konard\",\"id\":1431904,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/konard\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"created_at\":\"2026-06-24T12:28:03Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-06-24T12:28:03Z\",\"body\":\"Revised this issue: the original draft proposed adding a new `HIVE_MIND_MIN_FREE_DISK_GB` var — that was incorrect. The absolute free-space gate **already exists** as `HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB` (`src/config.lib.mjs:114`, default 2048 MB, documented in `docs/CONFIGURATION.md:82`). The ask is now simply to change the two existing defaults to the safer values we run in production: `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` 0.9→**0.8** and `HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB` 2048→**10240** (10 GB). No new variable needed.\",\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"pin\":null,\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4789278821/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"minimized\":null},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4794414061\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1981#issuecomment-4794414061\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1981\",\"id\":4794414061,\"node_id\":\"IC_kwDOPUU0qc8AAAABHcTz7Q\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"konard\",\"id\":1431904,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/konard\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"created_at\":\"2026-06-24T23:13:16Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-06-24T23:13:16Z\",\"body\":\"We also need to make sure we switch HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD queue mode from rejection to regular wait. And also make `--isolation docker` default, instead of `--isolation screen`. As it is now stable and auto cleanups on success.\\n\\nWe need to collect data related about the issue to this repository, make sure we compile that data to `./docs/case-studies/issue-{id}` folder, and use it to do deep case study analysis (also make sure to search online for additional facts and data), list of each and all requirements from the issue, and propose possible solutions and solution plans for each requirement (we should also check known existing components/libraries, that solve similar problem or can help in solutions).\\n\\nPlease plan and execute everything in this single pull request, you have unlimited time and context, as context auto-compacts and you can continue indefinitely, until it is each and every requirement fully addressed, and everything is totally done.\",\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"pin\":null,\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/comments/4794414061/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"minimized\":null}]\n--\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-1-# Issue 1981: Safer Disk and Isolation Defaults\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-2-\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-3-## Summary\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-4-\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md:5:Issue #1981 asked for default-only hardening after production disk exhaustion caused isolated tasks to die. The existing gates were present, but their shipped defaults allowed work to start too late:\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-6-\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md:7:- Disk usage queue threshold: `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` default `0.9` -> `0.8`.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-8-- Absolute free-space gate: `HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB` default `2048` -> `10240`.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-9-- Disk threshold queue strategy: default immediate rejection -> normal wait/enqueue.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-10-- Isolation default: `--isolation screen` -> `--isolation docker`.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-11-\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-12-The implementation keeps the existing environment variables and CLI flags. No new `HIVE_MIND_MIN_FREE_DISK_GB` setting was added because `HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB` already provides the absolute free-space gate.\n--\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-25-- `test-logs/green-test-issue-1981.log` - same regression after implementation.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-26-- `test-logs/npm-ci.log` - dependency install log for this workspace.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-27-\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-28-## Requirements\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-29-\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md:30:1. Change `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` built-in default from `0.9` to `0.8` in both the primary `thresholds.disk` config and legacy `DISK_THRESHOLD` alias.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-31-2. Change `HIVE_MIND_MIN_DISK_SPACE_MB` built-in default from `2048` MB to `10240` MB.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-32-3. Do not add a new absolute free-space variable.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-33-4. Change the disk threshold default strategy from `reject` to regular wait/enqueue.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-34-5. Make Docker isolation the default instead of screen isolation.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-35-6. Update English and localized configuration docs.\n--\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-102-\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-103-### Implemented Plan\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-104-\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-105-Implemented Option A plus the later requirements:\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-106-\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md:107:- Updated queue disk default to `0.8` and default strategy to `enqueue`.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-108-- Updated absolute disk-space defaults to `10240` MB through shared config, memory checks, solve config, solve runtime fallback, and hive runtime fallback.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-109-- Updated Telegram bot isolation default to Docker while preserving `TELEGRAM_ISOLATION=` and `--isolation ''` opt-out.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-110-- Updated standalone task isolation default to Docker.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-111-- Updated `/stop` guidance that still recommended `--isolation screen`.\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1981/README.md-112-- Updated English, Hindi, Chinese, and Russian configuration docs.\n--\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1903/data/run-27332260596-test-execution-failed.txt-144-test-execution\tUNKNOWN STEP\t2026-06-11T07:54:20.7300784Z Updating files:  62% (2115/3411)\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1903/data/run-27332260596-test-execution-failed.txt-145-test-execution\tUNKNOWN STEP\t2026-06-11T07:54:20.7603848Z Updating files:  63% (2149/3411)\ndocs/case-studies/issue-1903/data/run-27332260596-test-execution-failed.txt-146-test-execution\tUNKNOWN STEP\t2026-06-11T07:54:20.7676374Z Updating files:  64% (2184/3411)\ndocs/case-studies/issue-190