tant/hive-mind/issues/2045/labels{/name}\",\n-  \"comments_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045/comments\",\n-  \"events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045/events\",\n-  \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045\",\n-  \"id\": 4862533972,\n-  \"node_id\": \"I_kwDOPUU0qc8AAAABIdRhVA\",\n-  \"number\": 2045,\n-  \"title\": \"Disk gate: change default HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD 0.8→0.65 for safer headroom on isolation hosts\",\n-  \"user\": { \"login\": \"konard\", \"id\": 1431904, \"node_id\": \"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\", \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\", \"gravatar_id\": \"\", \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard\", \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/konard\", \"followers_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers\", \"following_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\", \"gists_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\", \"starred_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}\", \"subscriptions_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions\", \"organizations_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs\", \"repos_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos\", \"events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}\", \"received_events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events\", \"type\": \"User\", \"user_view_type\": \"public\", \"site_admin\": false },\n-  \"labels\": [],\n-  \"state\": \"open\",\n-  \"locked\": false,\n-  \"assignees\": [],\n-  \"milestone\": null,\n-  \"comments\": 0,\n-  \"created_at\": \"2026-07-11T13:50:39Z\",\n-  \"updated_at\": \"2026-07-11T13:50:39Z\",\n-  \"closed_at\": null,\n-  \"assignee\": null,\n-  \"author_association\": \"MEMBER\",\n-  \"issue_field_values\": [],\n-  \"type\": null,\n-  \"active_lock_reason\": null,\n-  \"sub_issues_summary\": { \"total\": 0, \"completed\": 0, \"percent_completed\": 0 },\n-  \"issue_dependencies_summary\": { \"blocked_by\": 0, \"total_blocked_by\": 0, \"blocking\": 0, \"total_blocking\": 0 },\n-  \"body\": \"## Request\\n\\nChange the default disk queue-admission threshold from **0.8 → 0.65**.\\n\\n`HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` currently defaults to `0.8` (set in #1981, raised from the older `0.9`). In practice `0.8` still leaves too little headroom on disk-constrained isolation hosts — tasks continue to be launched at 80% used and then die at ~100% while a `--isolation docker` task expands images/scratch. Operators keep having to manually lower it to `0.65` in their env to get a safe margin.\\n\\n## Where\\n\\n`src/queue-config.lib.mjs`:\\n\\n```js\\n// line ~250 (thresholds.disk)\\ndisk: getThresholdConfig('disk', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_STRATEGY', 0.8, 'enqueue'),\\n// line ~266 (legacy flat DISK_THRESHOLD)\\nDISK_THRESHOLD: getThresholdConfig('disk', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_STRATEGY', 0.8, 'enqueue').value,\\n```\\n\\nBoth `0.8` default literals should become `0.65`.\\n\\n## Why 0.65\\n\\n- `--isolation docker` tasks need substantial free disk for image layers + per-task scratch; starting at 80% used routinely fills the host before a task completes.\\n- `0.65` is the value operators already fall back to manually (e.g. the hive-control-center deployment), so making it the default removes a required override.\\n- The `enqueue` strategy is unchanged — tasks wait rather than being rejected, so a lower threshold just means the bot backs off earlier and resumes once disk frees up.\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\n- Update the two default literals above.\\n- Update any doc/comment referencing the `0.8` default (e.g. the `Issue #1981` comment block).\\n- No env-var/API change — operators can still override via `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` or `HIVE_MIND_QUEUE_CONFIG`.\\n\\nFollow-up to #1981.\\n\",\n-  \"closed_by\": null,\n-  \"reactions\": { \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045/reactions\", \"total_count\": 0, \"+1\": 0, \"-1\": 0, \"laugh\": 0, \"hooray\": 0, \"confused\": 0, \"heart\": 0, \"rocket\": 0, \"eyes\": 0 },\n-  \"timeline_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045/timeline\",\n-  \"performed_via_github_app\": null,\n-  \"state_reason\": null,\n-  \"pinned_comment\": null\n-}\n+{\"author\":{\"id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"is_bot\":false,\"login\":\"konard\",\"name\":\"Konstantin Diachenko\"},\"body\":\"## Request\\n\\nChange the default disk queue-admission threshold from **0.8 → 0.65**.\\n\\n`HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` currently defaults to `0.8` (set in #1981, raised from the older `0.9`). In practice `0.8` still leaves too little headroom on disk-constrained isolation hosts — tasks continue to be launched at 80% used and then die at ~100% while a `--isolation docker` task expands images/scratch. Operators keep having to manually lower it to `0.65` in their env to get a safe margin.\\n\\n## Where\\n\\n`src/queue-config.lib.mjs`:\\n\\n```js\\n// line ~250 (thresholds.disk)\\ndisk: getThresholdConfig('disk', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_STRATEGY', 0.8, 'enqueue'),\\n// line ~266 (legacy flat DISK_THRESHOLD)\\nDISK_THRESHOLD: getThresholdConfig('disk', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD', 'HIVE_MIND_DISK_STRATEGY', 0.8, 'enqueue').value,\\n```\\n\\nBoth `0.8` default literals should become `0.65`.\\n\\n## Why 0.65\\n\\n- `--isolation docker` tasks need substantial free disk for image layers + per-task scratch; starting at 80% used routinely fills the host before a task completes.\\n- `0.65` is the value operators already fall back to manually (e.g. the hive-control-center deployment), so making it the default removes a required override.\\n- The `enqueue` strategy is unchanged — tasks wait rather than being rejected, so a lower threshold just means the bot backs off earlier and resumes once disk frees up.\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\n- Update the two default literals above.\\n- Update any doc/comment referencing the `0.8` default (e.g. the `Issue #1981` comment block).\\n- No env-var/API change — operators can still override via `HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD` or `HIVE_MIND_QUEUE_CONFIG`.\\n\\nFollow-up to #1981.\\n\",\"comments\":[],\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-11T13:50:39Z\",\"labels\":[],\"number\":2045,\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"Disk gate: change default HIVE_MIND_DISK_THRESHOLD 0.8→0.65 for safer headroom on isolation hosts\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-07-11T13:50:39Z\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2045\"}\ndiff --git a/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr-review-comments.json b/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr-review-comments.json\nindex fe51488c..0637a088 100644\n--- a/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr-review-comments.json\n+++ b/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr-review-comments.json\n@@ -1 +1 @@\n-[]\n+[]\n\\ No newline at end of file\ndiff --git a/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr-reviews.json b/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr-reviews.json\nindex fe51488c..0637a088 100644\n--- a/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr-reviews.json\n+++ b/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr-reviews.json\n@@ -1 +1 @@\n-[]\n+[]\n\\ No newline at end of file\ndiff --git a/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr.json b/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr.json\nindex 335c4414..8048c8ae 100644\n--- a/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr.json\n+++ b/dev/log/issues/2045/pulls/2046/pr.json\n@@ -1,306 +1 @@\n-{\n-  \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/pulls/2046\",\n-  \"id\": 4035888748,\n-  \"node_id\": \"PR_kwDOPUU0qc7wjsZs\",\n-  \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/2046\",\n-  \"diff_url\": \"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/2046.diff\",\n-  \"patch_url\": \"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/2046.patch\",\n-  \"issue_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2046\",\n-  \"number\": 2046,\n-  \"sta